question: List all actors with their IDs and names.
expected_sql: SELECT actor_id, first_name, last_name FROM actor;

question: Add a new actor named 'John Doe'.
expected_sql: INSERT INTO actor (first_name, last_name) VALUES ('John', 'Doe');

question: Update the last name of actor with ID 1 to 'Smith'.
expected_sql: UPDATE actor SET last_name = 'Smith' WHERE actor_id = 1;

question: Delete the actor with ID 2.
expected_sql: DELETE FROM actor WHERE actor_id = 2;

question: Show all films and their descriptions.
expected_sql: SELECT film_id, title, description FROM film;

question: Insert a new film titled 'New Movie' in language 1.
expected_sql: INSERT INTO film (title, language_id) VALUES ('New Movie', 1);

question: Change the rating of film ID 3 to 'PG-13'.
expected_sql: UPDATE film SET rating = 'PG-13' WHERE film_id = 3;

question: Remove the film with ID 4.
expected_sql: DELETE FROM film WHERE film_id = 4;

question: Retrieve all categories.
expected_sql: SELECT category_id, name FROM category;

question: Add a new category 'Horror'.
expected_sql: INSERT INTO category (name) VALUES ('Horror');

question: Rename category ID 5 to 'Thriller'.
expected_sql: UPDATE category SET name = 'Thriller' WHERE category_id = 5;

question: Delete category with ID 6.
expected_sql: DELETE FROM category WHERE category_id = 6;

question: List all customers with their store and email.
expected_sql: SELECT customer_id, store_id, email FROM customer;

question: Create a new customer for store 1 named 'Alice Brown'.
expected_sql: INSERT INTO customer (store_id, first_name, last_name, create_date, address_id, active) VALUES (1, 'Alice', 'Brown', NOW(), 1, 1);

question: Update email of customer ID 10 to 'newemail@example.com'.
expected_sql: UPDATE customer SET email = 'newemail@example.com' WHERE customer_id = 10;

question: Remove customer with ID 11.
expected_sql: DELETE FROM customer WHERE customer_id = 11;

question: Show inventory items for film ID 5.
expected_sql: SELECT inventory_id, film_id, store_id FROM inventory WHERE film_id = 5;

question: Add a new inventory item for film 5 in store 2.
expected_sql: INSERT INTO inventory (film_id, store_id) VALUES (5, 2);

question: Update the store of inventory ID 20 to store 3.
expected_sql: UPDATE inventory SET store_id = 3 WHERE inventory_id = 20;

question: Delete inventory record with ID 21.
expected_sql: DELETE FROM inventory WHERE inventory_id = 21;
